"{\"uid\": \"sbs.com.au-news-article-historic-river-parade-launches-paris-olympics-oav2cvwlh\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Stream free online, anytime  Discover your world of SBS  Sign in or create an account  or  Stream free online, anytime  Get in touch:  Highlights around SBS:  Follow Us:  SBS acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of Country and their connections and continuous care for the skies, lands and waterways throughout Australia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 1.4206661715792276e-12, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony for the Paris Olympics got the 2024 Summer Games underway with a pulsating energy and a unique show.Source:Getty  The Paris Olympics' opening ceremony got underway after a rough start to the Summer Games, with rainy skies over the Seine andsuspected acts of sabotage targeting France's flagship high-speed rail network.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7095878462794958e-30, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 624, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3835874615033116e-14, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 300,000 spectators lined the banks of the river, in the first time the opening ceremony had been staged outside the main stadium, making it the biggest-ever launch for an Olympic event.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 organiser Tony Estanguet had said the opening ceremony needed to \\\"push the limits as far as possible\\\", showing from the start France's ambition for the Games.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.249977259061532e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3835874615033116e-14, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are some of the highlights of the ceremony:  Opening ceremony mastermind Thomas Jolly, a renowned French theatre director, had carefully choreographed every minute of the festival along the banks of the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.6612766416317621, \"rank\": 0.36060655042466094, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 1139, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5569382399667312, \"rank\": 0.7946907777541343, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there was one factor he could not plan for - the weather.\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony had the misfortune to take place amid heavy showers descending on Paris, even as forecasts showed days of hot sunny weather ahead.\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1408, \"end\": 1413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5354962012043946e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators, VIPs, and athletes alike found themselves drenched or huddling in transparent ponchos.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some spectators refused to let the downpour get them down.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1632, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have got such an adrenaline rush.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's very exciting,\\\" said Selene Martinez, 42, who had travelled from Mexico for the ceremony.\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1696, \"end\": 1702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selene\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8306407343440046e-22, \"text\": \"Selene\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selene\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selene\"}, {\"begin\": 1703, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tippy_Martinez\", \"score\": 0.9999999215142483, \"rank\": 7.845798470904803e-08, \"text\": \"Martinez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tippy_Martinez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tippy_Martinez\"}, {\"begin\": 1740, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9999999999827196, \"rank\": 1.585393079191196e-11, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But others were less stoic about the heavy rain on the parade, with some leaving the ceremony early to seek shelter.\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a great idea.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The performances are awesome.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just wish it wasn't raining,\\\" said Pauline Brett, 69, who had come from Chicago with her family.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1971, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999995582867153, \"rank\": 4.417129357307478e-07, \"text\": \"Pauline\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 2008, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3561504067960437e-13, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French soccer legend Zinedine Zidane kicked off the opening ceremony with the Olympic flame in his hands.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2034, \"end\": 2040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5569382399667312, \"rank\": 0.7946907777541343, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a pre-recorded video, he ran through a Parisian traffic jam before delivering the flame to a group of children on the metro who then made their way through the Catacombs and to a boat, at which point the broadcast switched to a real-time view of the Seine River.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2304, \"end\": 2313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catacombs_of_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.8654949306986825e-11, \"text\": \"Catacombs\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catacombs_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catacombs_of_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zidane, Serena Williams, Rafael Nadal, Carl Lewis and Nadia Comaneci were among the greats to shepherd the flame to its destination.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2408, \"end\": 2414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.155989264676747e-23, \"text\": \"Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 2433, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 2462, \"end\": 2476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"score\": 0.9999999839874364, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadia Comaneci\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Charles Coste, the oldest French Olympic champion at 100, took the Olympic flame from his wheelchair and passed it to French judo great Teddy Riner and sprinter Marie-Jose Perec.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Coste\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Coste\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Coste\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Coste\"}, {\"begin\": 2568, \"end\": 2574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5569382399667312, \"rank\": 0.7946907777541343, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5569382399667312, \"rank\": 0.7946907777541343, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2678, \"end\": 2689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}, {\"begin\": 2703, \"end\": 2719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999290594, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cauldron was lit by Perec and Riner.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other notable Olympians who played an influential role included Tony Parker and Amelie Mauresmo.\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2827, \"end\": 2838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Parker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.50592809954061e-19, \"text\": \"Tony Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Parker\"}, {\"begin\": 2843, \"end\": 2858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Am\\u00e9lie_Mauresmo\", \"score\": 0.9999999998108251, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amelie Mauresmo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Am\\u00e9lie_Mauresmo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Am\\u00e9lie_Mauresmo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame lifted 30 metres into the Parisian night sky in a hot air balloon, as Canadian singer Celine Dion sang Hymne A l'Amour under the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2941, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.8502880900511908, \"rank\": 0.17607019172443378, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2957, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7960372610218536e-54, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, Dion, who has been battling a debilitating rare neurological condition, had vowed she would fight her way back from the disease that has kept her off-stage.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a social media post on X, Dion said she was \\\"honoured\\\" to perform at the opening ceremony and \\\"full of joy\\\" to be back in Paris.\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3310, \"end\": 3315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5354962012043946e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A historic boat parade down the River Seine launched the Paris Olympics with spectacular French flair, as the City of Light welcomed the world's greatest athletes.\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3350, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5569382399667312, \"rank\": 0.7946907777541343, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Led out by Greece through jets of water cascading from a bridge, accompanied by an accordion player, around 7,000 athletes cruised down a 6km stretch of the Seine to the Eiffel Tower on 85 boats.\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3494, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999089481279917, \"rank\": 9.106016301821782e-05, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7095878462794958e-30, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Braving the heavy rain, some 300,000 people lined the river banks to cheer on the armada carrying competitors past the city's iconic sights: the Eiffel Tower bearing the five Olympic rings, the Louvre and Notre Dame Cathedral.\", \"from\": 3680, \"to\": 3906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3874, \"end\": 3880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9999939854232139, \"rank\": 6.0146130470004925e-06, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 85 boats carried the team delegations on a four-mile journey through the centre of Paris, with more than 300,000 spectators watching from the riverside and bridges.\", \"from\": 3908, \"to\": 4083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4002, \"end\": 4007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5354962012043946e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rapper Snoop Dogg also carried the Olympic flame through a Parisian suburb on Friday morning, while a masked torchbearer ran with the flame over the Paris rooftops.\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4092, \"end\": 4102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 4234, \"end\": 4239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5354962012043946e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The anonymous torchbearer first appeared in a boat to the music of the Phantom of the Opera and then traversed the rooftops of Paris, weaving through iconic landmarks like the Louvre and Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay.\", \"from\": 4251, \"to\": 4452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4378, \"end\": 4383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5354962012043946e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4438, \"end\": 4451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\", \"score\": 0.9999999943702278, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His identity is yet to be revealed.\", \"from\": 4454, \"to\": 4489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American singer surprised viewers by singing in French next to the River Seine during her performance, which saw her deliver a burlesque take on the French classic Mon Truc En Plume.\", \"from\": 4491, \"to\": 4677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4495, \"end\": 4503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999940310774, \"rank\": 5.968781102927113e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4562, \"end\": 4573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 4644, \"end\": 4658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 38-year-old has said it was her \\\"supreme honour\\\" to perform at the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This song was sung by Zizi Jeanmaire, born in Paris a French ballerina, she famously sang Mon Truc en Plumes in 1961\\\", Gaga said.\", \"from\": 4784, \"to\": 4914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4807, \"end\": 4821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"score\": 1.